(46, 8, 9, 61, 2, 19, 19, 'liberty', 'Liberty and Bondage Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of liberty and its potential consequences. Both passages emphasize how liberty can lead to bondage, either through causing others to stumble or through being overcome by corruption.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(46, 8, 9, 45, 14, 1, 2, 'this liberty of yours become a stumblingblock', 'Liberty and Weakness in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of considering the weak in faith. In 1 Corinthians, the warning is about liberty becoming a stumblingblock, while Romans discusses receiving the weak and their dietary choices.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
