(46, 8, 10, 4, 25, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Idolatry and Conscience', 'Both passages emphasize the act of eating in relation to idols. In 1 Corinthians, the concern is about the conscience of the weak being influenced by others eating in an idol''s temple, while Numbers describes people eating sacrifices to their gods, indicating a direct link to idolatrous practices.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
