(46, 8, 13, 47, 6, 3, 3, 'make my brother to offend', 'Avoiding Offense in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not causing offense to others. In 1 Corinthians 8:13, Paul expresses a commitment to avoid actions that might lead others to stumble, while 2 Corinthians 6:3 highlights the need to give no offense to protect the integrity of the ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
